### Input validation rules
- All user input validated at: — _(route layer / middleware / controller)_
- Validation library: —
- Required on: all POST/PUT/PATCH bodies, query params used in DB queries, file uploads
- Never trust: client-provided IDs for ownership checks, user-supplied file paths, raw HTML input

### Attack surface
_AI: Known entry points that need active hardening. Fill as the project grows._

| Surface | Risk | Mitigation in place |
|---------|------|-------------------|
| — | — | — |

### Security forbidden patterns
> These are in addition to the CODE QUALITY forbidden list. Hard blocks — never produce this code.

- No raw SQL with user input. Parameterized queries always.
- No `innerHTML` with unsanitized data. Use `textContent` or a sanitizer.
- No auth checks in the client only. Server must validate every protected request.
- No secrets in environment-committed files. Only in `.env` (gitignored).
- No predictable IDs for sensitive resources. Use UUIDs or tokens.
- No verbose error messages exposed to the client. Log server-side, return generic message.
- No passwords stored in plaintext or with reversible encryption. Use bcrypt / argon2.

